  "prompt": "Why is there no hug emoticon on WhatsApp?",
  "response": "WhatsApp, like many messaging platforms, has a limited set of emoticons and emojis to choose from. While a \"hug\" emoji exists in the standard Unicode Emoji set (specifically the \"\ud83e\udd17\" Face with Open Hands emoji), WhatsApp may not have chosen to include it prominently in their interface or it may not be as widely recognized or used compared to other emojis.\n\nHowever, you can still send a hug emoji in WhatsApp by accessing your device's emoji keyboard and selecting the \"\ud83e\udd17\" emoji. It might not be as instantly noticeable as some other emoticons because WhatsApp's design and updates are influenced by user demand, design preferences, and platform limitations.\n\nIf you're looking for a way to send a hug through WhatsApp and can't find the \u201c\ud83e\udd17\u201d emoji quickly, you can also use other ways to express affection, such as text, stickers, or GIFs.",
